.TH APT\-CACHER\-RS 8 "May 2026" "apt-cacher-rs" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
apt\-cacher\-rs \- caching proxy for Debian style package repositories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B apt\-cacher\-rs
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B apt\-cacher\-rs
is a caching HTTP proxy for APT-style package repositories, written in
Rust. It sits between APT clients and upstream Debian or Ubuntu mirrors,
transparently storing downloaded packages, indexes and metadata so that
subsequent requests are served from the local cache without re-fetching
them over the network.

It is intended as a smaller, faster and memory-safe alternative to
apt-cacher-ng for hosts that need to share package downloads across
multiple machines.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c\  PATH ", " \-\-config\-file= PATH
Configuration file path
.RI ( default :
.IR /etc/apt\-cacher\-rs/apt\-cacher\-rs.conf ).
.TP
.BI \-\-cache\-path= PATH
Cache directory path; overrides
.I cache_directory
from the configuration file.
.TP
.BI \-\-database\-path= PATH
Database file path; overrides
.I database_path
from the configuration file.
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-file= PATH
Log file path. Logs are written to the given file instead of the
console (the default).
.TP
.BI \-l\  SEVERITY ", " \-\-log\-level= SEVERITY
Logging level (e.g. \fItrace\fR, \fIdebug\fR, \fIinfo\fR, \fIwarn\fR,
\fIerror\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-log\-timestamp
Do not include a timestamp in log messages. Useful when the service
manager (such as systemd) already adds one.
.TP
.B \-\-permit\-running\-daemon\-as\-root
Permit the daemon to run as the root user. This is potentially
dangerous and is not recommended.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a help summary and exit.
.TP
.B \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apt\-cacher\-rs/apt\-cacher\-rs.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/cache/apt\-cacher\-rs/
Default cache directory.
.TP
.I /var/lib/apt\-cacher\-rs/apt\-cacher\-rs.db
Default database file.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Reopen the log file (when logging to a file).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apt (8),
.BR systemd.service (5).
.PP
Project homepage:
